[SN]TITLE[SN]
Army working to make London WW2 bomb safe

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bomb disposal experts have been working through the night to make a WW2 bomb found in north-west London safe.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
3 March 2017 Last updated at 10:31 GMT
The 500lb (227kg) device was discovered on a building site in The Avenue, Brondesbury Park.
Nearby residents have been evacuated and a 300m cordon put in place while teams prepare to move the bomb.
